history.content:
The waitlist is processed in order of the (lecture) waitlist. If there is space in the class, the first student on the waitlist who can get into the class, does so. Students who are waitlisted for a full section can't get into the class, so they would be skipped, yes.

For your second question, see @1749.

In general for students on the waitlist, are those that selected a still open section enrolled before those that selected a filled section?

If this is the case, since Calcentral doesn't allow you to switch your section for classes you've waitlisted, is there anything a student that signed up for a filled section can do?
history.subject: Getting off Waitlists in General
